VALUES (currval(pg_get_serial_sequence('medical_documents', 'id')), 1, 'make informed decisions about their management. Hair is deeply intertwined with a person’s identity. Hair loss therefore can have a profound psychological impact and induce feelings of low self-worth, lack of physical attractiveness and fear of social rejection. In brief, the hair cycle consists of 3 main phases: anagen (growth), catagen (transitional) and telogen (resting), with hair follicles cycling between these stages to produce and shed hair over time. In AGA, alterations in the hair cycle include shortening of anagen and lengthening of telogen, resulting in reduced hair growth. There are 2 forms of alopecia: scarring (where the follicles are permanently lost) and non-scarring. AGA is a non-scarring alopecia. As the follicular unit is preserved, AGA is considered at least partially reversible. The prevalence of AGA increases with age. Male pattern hair loss is thought to affect 80% of males by the age of 80. Both males and females with AGA report hair thinning.', '{0.1945142298936844,-0.24233239889144897,0.24777649343013763,-0.29530656337738037,0.25689536333084106,0.5039618015289307,0.2953627109527588,-0.18018215894699097,-0.1492830365896225,-0.350818932056427,0.04720482975244522,1.0731490850448608,-0.018825476989150047,0.1784941852092743,0.12985418736934662,0.37821266055107117,0.572996199131012,0.18710313737392426,-0.4360716938972473,-0.8302936553955078,-0.4881722331047058,0.9975011348724365,0.06761030852794647,0.4896223545074463,0.1297268271446228,-0.7050260901451111,-0.7256677150726318,0.41689085960388184,-0.1754346340894699,-0.10834378004074097,-0.696317732334137,-0.6182098984718323,-0.11919059604406357,-0.06608504056930542,0.013606948778033257,0.35326266288757324,0.23114079236984253,0.2817951440811157,0.2716688811779022,0.44073736667633057,0.000577322265598923,-0.32135239243507385,-0.6401911973953247,-0.15813390910625458,0.3581906855106354,0.9463769793510437,0.4439087212085724,0.12511